post_text: Details for morning drop off at Forsan JH/HS: Sixth graders not eating breakfast at school will go in near the auditorium and will be seated in the auditorium since band is first period (they'll be close to the band hall). Any student that is eating breakfast at school and any students being dropped off by parents will come in the cafeteria doors. Buses will drop off between the gyms and field house. 7th and 8th graders have athletics in that area (field houses and/or gyms). High school students that are not eating breakfast will be seated by grade level in the game gym. Our high school students that get here at the last possible second can still come in the front doors. :) Can't wait to see everyone tomorrow!

¿Recibió su hijo comidas escolares gratuitas o a precio reducido a través del Programa Nacional de
Almuerzos Escolares durante el año escolar 2019-2020? Si es así, su familia puede ser elegible para la
Transferencia Electrónica de Beneficios durante la Pandemia (Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer, PEBT) para comprar alimentos. Presente su solicitud hasta el 30 de junio de 2020. Las familias elegibles
deben haber recibido el enlace a la solicitud de las escuelas. Las familias elegibles que recibieron los
beneficios del SNAP para marzo ya han recibido los beneficios de la P-EBT y no tienen que presentar una
solicitud. Si no recibió un enlace a la solicitud o tiene preguntas sobre el programa, comuníquese con el
Centro de Atención al Cliente de la P-EBT llamando al 833-613-6220, de lunes a viernes, de 8:00 a. m. a
6:00 p. m.

Did your child receive free or reduced-price school meals through the National School Lunch Program
during the 2019-2020 school year? If so, your family may be eligible for P-EBT benefits to buy food.
Apply by June 30, 2020.
Eligible families that received SNAP benefits for March have already received P-EBT benefits and do not
have to apply. If you did not receive an application link or have questions about the program, please
contact the P-EBT Call Center at 833-613-6220 Monday through Friday, 8:00 am – 6:00 pm.

It is time for the 2020 Census!

Did you know that Howard County's response rate is under 47%? 😱

Did you know that the census response determines federal funding for many programs? 💸

Did you know that census results determine how many seats Texas will be allocated in the House of Representatives? 🏛

Did you know that $1.5 trillion are allocated to public schools, roads, hospitals, and public works? 🛣

Did you know it is quick and easy to respond?😀

Simply go to www.my2020census.gov and answer the quick survey. It only takes a few minutes to respond, and the results are applicable for ten years!

Forsan JH/HS Families:

You may drop off chromebooks, instruments, library books, athletic equipment, etc., and pick up contents of lockers from 9:00 to 11:00 and 2:00 to 4:00 on these dates:

Tue, May 12 - Juniors and Seniors
Wed, May 13 - Freshmen and Sophomores
Thu, May 14 - 7th and 8th Grades
Fri, May 15 - 6th Grade

We will put everything in the old gym with one way in and one way out from the west side. We'll have signs and people outside to guide you. Bins will be available for drop off items, and we'll have lockers bagged up and organized alphabetically. We will follow social distancing guidelines and allow one person in the gym at a time for drop off and pick up.

May 1 at 11:39 AM ·

We have 403 reasons to return to school, but see our 44 biggest reasons in our Senior Spotlights.

Senior Spotlight: Celsia Sanchez

Message from Celsia:

After I graduate I plan to gain my education at Howard College. I want to enter college striving to receive my LVN license, and then proceed to receive my RN license. My main goal is to become a successful maternity nurse. In my spare time I enjoy spending time with family, coloring while listening to music, and making breakfast. One fact that I can share about myself is that as a senior I worked on receiving my CNA license. I can say it was well worth the time and effort. Through this process I’ve gained knowledge, appreciation, and understanding on what it takes to become a successful nurse. I’ve always had a tremendous heart towards helping others. I can honestly say I’ve gained a greater passion for nursing.

post_text:
To the Forsan ISD Students and Parents,

Governor Greg Abbott announced today that schools in Texas would not reopen their school facilities for this current school year but would continue the education of our students through distance learning. Although this saddens us, his goal of keeping us all safe makes this decision understandable. We will soon announce plans for graduation of our 2020 senior class. We will gradually make other announcements related to end-of-school activities. But first, there are about five weeks of school remaining. We want all of our students to reach their full potential and to accomplish their goals. A serious approach to school work and a “finish strong” attitude are both important in these last few weeks.

“Dare to be Great!”

Randy Johnson
Superintendent
Forsan ISD

From CharacterStrong :

Submit a "Teacher Appreciation" Video

Many teachers are having a difficult time right now because they miss being with their students in the classroom, so together, let's let them know how much they mean to us!

Think of a teacher who has made a big impact on you and film a video in under 30-seconds telling them one specific thing you're grateful that they taught you, and how much you appreciate the role they've played in your life. Speak as if you were talking directly to them, and be as specific as possible.

We're going to compile submissions into one video to share with educators all across the country! Thank you for participating :)

Practice Social Distancing

To avoid the spread of COVID-19 in our community, practice social distancing:
• Avoid going out in public.
• When in public, keep six feet of distance between you and others.
• Follow guidance provided by local and state officials.
Get more information at https://texas.gov/covid19

Practica el distanciamiento social

Para prevenir la propagación de COVID-19 en nuestra comunidad, practique el distanciamiento social:
• Evite salir en público.
• Cuando esté en público, mantenga una distancia de seis pies entre usted y los demás.
• Seguir las recomendaciones de los funcionarios locales y estatales.

Texas Health and Human Services has launched a 24/7 statewide mental health support line to help Texans experiencing anxiety, stress or emotional challenges due to the COVID-19 pandemic.

This new resource offers COVID-19-related mental health support for all Texans. People can call the Statewide COVID-19 Mental Health Support Line 24 hours a day, 7 days a week toll-free at 833-986-1919.

Operated by the Harris Center for Mental Health and IDD, the support line offers trauma-informed support and psychological first aid to those experiencing stress and anxiety related to COVID-19.

Positive Message for the Week (from Stay Positive by Gordon and Decker):

Faith and fear have one thing in common besides the letter F. They both believe in a future that hasn't happened yet. Fear believes in a negative future. Faith believes in a positive future. If neither has happened yet, why wouldn't we choose to believe in a positive future?

Question of the Week:

If money was not an issue, how would you spend your time?

post_text:
Dear Forsan JH/HS Families:

Our staff met this morning to review the latest information from the Texas Education Agency and the Centers for Disease Control. Teachers and paraprofessionals began planning the best ways to provide instruction to our students. One of our goals is to determine very soon which of our students have access to a device/internet. Watch for a survey this week. We will adjust provision of lessons based on students' ability to use google classroom and/or teachers' websites for updates and assignments. We must also be sure to provide the accommodations and modifications needed for our students that receive special education services. Teachers began today reaching out to students through existing communication channels such as google classroom. We will continue that through the week and begin providing lessons. We miss our students and want them to know that we are thinking about them and their families. Please let us know if you have any questions: 432-457-2223.

Hanna Carter
Forsan JH/HS Principal

January 21 at 2:13 PM ·

Today at our Tuesday Rotary Club our President Laurie Barraza open up our meeting and proceeded to inform us about upcoming events for February. Next see introduced Thomas Padilla our Educational Chairperson to present the Student of the month. The Student of the Month is Mallory Ezell from Forsan High School. Next Angela Sarmiengo introduced the Speaker of the Day which was our own Clearance Hartfield. Clearance talked about his experience in the Military during the Martin Luther King days.

Applications for the National Youth Science Camp are open. This all-expense paid camp for graduating seniors brings together talented students from all fifty states.

To be selected, a student must be a graduating high school senior. The NYSCamp will be held from June 22 to July 15, 2020. Students must be able to attend the entire program.

The deadline to submit applications is 5:00 PM on February 28, 2020.

Additional information is available at https://nysf.smapply.io/.

post_text:
We wanted to say congratulations to our 8th grade Art Smart team. These four students have competed together as a team since the 4th grade and, on Friday, they won their 5th consecutive gold medal. This is the last year that they will be able to compete and we are so proud of all of their hard work. Way to go!! 🥇🖤🥇

Pictured: Hilary Thompson, Jaci Stone, Lilly Hoff and Avery Williams

Special thanks to their UIL coaches for helping them reach this accomplishment: Mrs. Seal, Mrs. Moellendorf and Mrs. Jones.
